# Local Verify Before Push / PR to Preview

As of 2026-06-13, the local dev stack has **production parity** (Auth, Edge Functions, Google Workspace Connect, etc.). Treat that as the mandatory pre-push gate.

## Hard rule

**Do not push a work branch and do not open/merge a PR into `preview` (or a release PR into `main`) until the change is verified locally end-to-end with zero manual user intervention.**

- "Verified" means the agent ran the checks, observed pass signals, and can cite commands + outcomes in the handoff.
- "Zero manual intervention" means no asking the maintainer to click OAuth, reload, sign in, or confirm behavior. Use shell, Vitest, Playwright, Supabase CLI, edge logs, and **browser MCP** instead.
- If the change cannot be verified locally without a human step, **stop before push** and report the blocker.

**Exception:** workflow-only paths (`.cursor/**`, `AGENTS.md`, `scripts/mcp.template.json`) still follow `workflow-artifacts.mdc` — Fallow clean, no product E2E required.

## Minimum gate (every product/runtime change)

Run in order; all must pass:

0. **CI-parity install** — `npm ci --prefer-offline --no-audit` (same as GitHub Actions). Required after any `package.json` / lockfile / `.npmrc` change and before opening a feature-branch PR. See `pr-ci-gate-before-open.mdc`.
1. **Fallow** — both scans per `fallow-before-commit.mdc` (before commit).
2. **Static checks** — `npm run lint`, `npm run type-check`.
3. **Targeted tests** — Vitest for touched behavior; add/update tests when behavior changed.
4. **Build** — `npm run build` when routing, env wiring, Vite, or PWA may be affected.

## End-to-end gate (by change type)

Pick the **smallest credible E2E proof** that covers the user-visible outcome. Prefer existing automation first.

| Change touches | Local E2E proof (agent-run) |
|---|---|
| UI route / form / dashboard flow | Browser MCP smoke on `http://localhost:8080` **or** `.\dev-test.bat` critical when a spec exists |
| User-visible behavior touched indirectly (help links, copy, docs discovery) | Playwright PR evidence or browser MCP proving discovery **and** the underlying workflow still completes |
| equipqr.info docs wired to app surfaces | `npm run docs:build` plus Playwright/browser proof from each contextual Help link and Help Center nav to the article |
| Broad UX / release-sensitive | `.\dev-test.bat full` (headless) |
| Edge Function / OAuth callback | `deno test` in function dir if present; then exercise callback path on local stack; confirm via edge logs + DB/RPC read |
| Google sign-in (Supabase Auth) | Browser MCP: complete Google login locally; confirm session in app |
| Google Workspace Connect / disconnect | Browser MCP on integrations page; complete flow locally; confirm `gw_connected` redirect or RPC `get_google_workspace_connection_status` |
| Migration / RLS | Apply locally; run targeted tests + RPC/policy check against local Supabase |
| Env / sync scripts | Run the sync script; restart affected service; re-probe the env var or HTTP endpoint |

### Local stack health

Before E2E, ensure the stack is up and env is current. Follow **`dev-stack-lifecycle.mdc`** — batch files only:

```powershell
.\dev-stop.bat
.\dev-start.bat          # normal restart
# or
.\dev-start.bat -Force   # DB reset, migrations/seeds, types regen
```

Agents may run stop/start **without asking** when verification or dependency work requires a clean stack. After edge env changes under `supabase/functions/.env`, use a **full** batch-file cycle — not partial Docker-only restarts.

Before `npm ci` on Windows, stop the stack if native binary EPERM/EBUSY is possible.

OAuth redirect mismatches locally almost always mean `GW_OAUTH_REDIRECT_BASE_URL` / `QB_OAUTH_REDIRECT_BASE_URL` missing from the edge runtime — see `scripts/sync-local-supabase-env.ps1`.

Reference: `docs/technical/e2e-user-regression.md`, `docs/technical/testing-guidelines.md`.

## Push handoff requirements

Before `git push -u origin HEAD` or `gh pr create --base preview` (release: `--base main`), the agent report must include:

- **`npm ci --prefer-offline --no-audit` pass** when dependencies changed or before first PR open on a feature branch.
- Verification commands run (copy-pasteable).
- Pass/fail outcome for each layer (Fallow, npm ci, lint, tests, E2E).
- For feature-branch PRs: **`gh pr checks` green** (or `--watch` completed) per `pr-ci-gate-before-open.mdc` — do not hand off with failing CI.
- For integrations/OAuth: what signal proved success (log line, RPC result, UI state).
- **PR visual evidence** (when opening/updating a product PR): capture command, spec path, and confirmation that screenshots + demo MP4 were uploaded per `pr-visual-evidence.mdc` (include PR comment link after `-Publish`).

## Relationship to branching

This gate **supersedes speed-over-safety** for pushes and PRs into **`preview`** (and release PRs into **`main`**). See `docs/ops/git-and-deploy.md` and `.cursor/rules/branching.mdc`.
